text:
There are times that you want to display something different based in some variable and for that one of the options would be to use "switch" when you don't want to use many if,else if,etc.
And since you can't use code in the html , angular has the ngSwitch for that here is how:

[code] 
//Ts File
import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-how-to-use-switch',
  templateUrl: './how-to-use-switch.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./how-to-use-switch.component.css'],
})
export class HowToUseSwitchComponent implements OnInit {
  linkin: string = 'https://image.flaticon.com/icons/png/512/174/174857.png';
  github: string = 'https://image.flaticon.com/icons/png/512/25/25231.png';
  constructor() {}

  ngOnInit(): void {}
  //Get the current value and based on that then display different Ui
  getCurrentValue(): string {
    return 'Git';
  }
}
[/code]
[code] 
//Html
<div>
  <!-- The parent would be the one with the ngswitch -->
  <div [ngSwitch]="getCurrentValue()">
    <!-- Check for simple string in this case is just 1  -->
    <div *ngSwitchCase="1">
      <p>Display Linkin!</p>
      <br />
      <img src="{{ linkin }}" alt="linkin" style="height: 200px;" />
    </div>
    <!-- To check for strings you add the ' ' -->
    <div *ngSwitchCase="'Git'">
      <p><b>Display github!</b></p>
      <br />
      <img src="{{ github }}" alt="linkin" style="height: 200px;" />
    </div>
    <p *ngSwitchCase="3">Some other Display :D</p>
    <!-- ngSwitchDefault gets display if the other cases didn't match -->
    <p *ngSwitchDefault>The Default Value or some error for not found</p>
  </div>
</div>
[/code]

This is how what it would display if you have:
 return '1':
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/oJfQiae.png"/>
 return 'Git':
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/KwRNkc1.png"/>
 return '3':
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/TuYwprV.png"/>
 return (any other value):
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/sAO2fjv.png"/>
For this example i'm just displaying some text with an image but you can use some other component or anything else you want to display.
